            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [is] to be cooked. Oil ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Helleborus) niger, Cissampelos pareira (Skt. pāṭha-), Trigonella foenum (graecum), Vaśira [flower or salt], Azadirachta indica, (root) of pipär ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... seed of (Holarrhana) antidysenterica, bean, Sanseviera zeylanica, Tinospora cordifolia, Agathotes chirata, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... this [is] to be cooked so that oil is left over. This oil ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">..., in case of jaundice, in case of redness, for the ones [infested with] worms, (for the ones) afflicted by heat ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... root of Piper longum, the three spices, the heart of the fruit of Aegle marmelos, Cissampelos pareira, [outer] skin (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [is] to be cooked. This oil is called the rich one [= Skt. dhānika-], it [is] to be drunk as a potion ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Nymphea stellata, aneth, Polygonatum verticillatum, Saccharum munja, Microstylis (muscifera) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a9"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... tr(au) [of] sa(liva) (?), eight trau [of] syrup, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for the ..., for the gal [diseases], for the abdomen tumors, ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for urine disease, for blood suffering, [this is] the invincible remedy ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Solanum indicum, Solanum xanthocarpum, Phaseolus trilobus, [in quantities of] half a trau per remedy ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for growing sight disorder. Ipomoea turpethum, the three myrobalans, Croton polyandrum, Acorus calamus, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... deodar, boiled rice, Piper chava, fruit of Calamus rotang: with that cooked o(il) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (so that an oil) [is] left over. This oil is called pañcakavvi (= Skt. pañcagavya 'five products of the cow'). (In case of) fever ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... two trau of deo(dar): 2, two trau of ginger: 2, fruit of Gmelina arborea ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (so that an oil is left) over. This oil (reache)s the nos(trils). The crown of the head [is] to be anointed. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b9"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for anyone indeed two trau ... during (one wee)k. This together with ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
