               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;This fragment is close to [[THT 497]], but not a direct parallel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; The reading and restoration &lt;i&gt;pepä[kṣu]&lt;/i&gt; by Filliozat is impossible since the upper part of the akṣara is to high for a ka. Furthermore one does not expect a PPt at the beginning of a clause. In addition, a phrase &lt;i&gt;pepärṣṣa witsäko&lt;/i&gt; recurs in [[PK AS 9C]] b3.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a5.&lt;/b&gt; Pace Filliozat, one has to read &lt;i&gt;paṇḍarokne&lt;/i&gt; for Skt. &lt;i&gt;paṇḍuroga&lt;/i&gt;- 'jaundice, lit. yellow disease'.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a6.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;dhanik&lt;/i&gt; is certainly a loan from Skt. &lt;i&gt;dha/ānika&lt;/i&gt;- 'rich, opulent' rather than 'coriander' in the present context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a7.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;panāk&lt;/i&gt; is certainly a loan from Skt. &lt;i&gt;pānaka&lt;/i&gt;- 'beverage, potion' (rather than Skt. &lt;i&gt;panaka&lt;/i&gt;- 'arum lily', which is poisonous). In this case, we should have a perlative of manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; One has to read &lt;i&gt;tallentse&lt;/i&gt;, not &lt;i&gt;tillentse&lt;/i&gt;, pace Filliozat. This forms calls to mind &lt;i&gt;talle&lt;/i&gt;* 'burden, load'. One may surmise a pseudo-compound 'burden pertaining to blood'. It may be a calque of a Sanskrit compound.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4.&lt;/b&gt; Since a form &lt;i&gt;tsämṣe&lt;/i&gt; gives no known word, one may surmise that the scribe omitted an akṣara, hence &lt;i&gt;tsämṣe‹ñcai›&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b5.&lt;/b&gt; One has to read &lt;i&gt;śärttākru&lt;/i&gt;, a variant of &lt;i&gt;śärtākru&lt;/i&gt; found in [[THT 497]] b8. It is certainly a loan from Sanskrit that can be restored as &lt;i&gt;śṛta-kuru-&lt;/i&gt; 'boiled rice'.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b8.&lt;/b&gt; We expect a verbal form ending in &lt;i&gt;ṣṣä〈ṃ〉&lt;/i&gt;. Unfortunately, it cannot be a form of &lt;i&gt;pin&lt;/i&gt;- 'blow (into the nose)', because we would expect a subjunctive. A possibility is to restore &lt;i&gt;(yänmā)ṣṣäṃ&lt;/i&gt; 'reaches', maybe as a cure involving inhalation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b9.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;ysā&lt;/i&gt; may be the start of a compound 'golden-x' or alternatively a noun with prefix &lt;i&gt;yä(n)&lt;/i&gt;-.&lt;/p&gt; </item>
